NAF.raw: http : / / broabandtrafficmanagement . blogspot . nl / 2011 / 10 / south - africa - p2p - control - helps - overcome . html TUESDAY , OCTOBER 11 , 2011 South Africa : P2P Control Helps Overcome Undersea Cable Outage "The SEACOM undersea cable , which provides a data link between South Africa , Europe and India , experienced downtime beginning on Saturday 8 October 2011 , caused by a problem on a cable between Abu Talat ( Egypt ) and Marseilles ( France ) . . Meanwhile , local Internet Service Providers ( ISPs ) who use bandwidth on the SEACOM cable have been scrambling to implement contingency plans to keep their customers connected" . According to an MWEB update - "Some more bandwidth was brought online last night [ 10 October 2011 ] bringing us up to 83% of our required capacity . We allowed P2P traffic to run from midnight to 7am , after which it had to give way for critical traffic again . " As MWEB also uses PeerApp's caching solution , it may help serve some P2P traffic without accessing the undersea cable .
